article.headline: Tennessee St. 59, Jacksonville St. 57
article.story: NASHVILLE, Tenn. -- Jerrell Houston hit a layup at the buzzer to lift Tennessee State to a 59-57 win over Jacksonville State on Thursday night. Houston, who finished with 12 points, grabbed the rebound off Gershom Jordan's miss for the game-winning basket as the Tigers (6-12, 4-5 Ohio Valley Conference) snapped a three-game losing streak. Houston's shot capped Tennessee State's comeback from a 55-46 deficit with 4:31 left in the game and sent Jacksonville State (8-9, 2-6) to its fifth straight loss. The Tigers led by 13 points in the first half, but the Gamecocks rallied to take a 44-41 lead on Jeremy Bynum's 3-pointer with 9:18 left in the game. Jacksonville State twice held nine-point leads in the final seven minutes. Jordan led the Tigers with 21 points and Gerald Robinson added 16. Brandon Crawford led the Gamecocks with 17 points.
